'''Ksar Medenine''' ([[Wikipedia:Arabic language|Arabic]]: قصر مدنين) is an old [[Wikipedia:Ksar|ksars]] in the town [[Wikipedia:Medenine|Medenine]] in southeastern [[Tunisia]], on the main route to [[Wikipedia:Libya|Libya]]. Medenine is the capital city of [[Wikipedia:Medenine Governorate|Medenine Governorate]]. Ksar Medenines was featured twice in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']]: first, when [[Anakin Skywalker]] leads his new friends to his home in the sand storm, and the second time when Anakin runs back to his mother, just before he goes with [[Qui-Gon Jinn]], both on the same location. It is one of three ksars around [[Wikipedia:Tataouine|Tataouine]] to represent the [[Slave Quarters Row/Legends|Slave Quarters Row]] on [[Tatooine]]. Ksar Medenine is located on av 7 Nevember.

